<h2 id="9Âº---next-step-is-to-create-the-swap-partition">9Âº - Next step is to create the SWAP partition:</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Type <code class="highlighter-rouge">a</code> again;</li>
  <li>Accept the letter <code class="highlighter-rouge">b</code> in brackets, just press [ENTER];</li>
  <li>The offset is default, press [ENTER];</li>
  <li>The <em>size</em> will show the rest of the remaining size, the size will appear in brackets, just press [ENTER];</li>
  <li>And finally <em>FS Type</em> will be <strong>swap</strong>, which will appear in brackets, ie, again just press [ENTER];</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="10Âº----ready-now-press-the-letter-w-write-to-save-the-changes">10Âº -  Ready, now press the letter <code class="highlighter-rouge">w</code> (write) to save the changes.</h2>

<p>If you want to see the layout after the changes, press the letter <code class="highlighter-rouge">p</code> and to exit and continue the installation press the letter<code class="highlighter-rouge"> q</code> and then [ENTER]. logical! =)</p>

